This is the Perl distribution Module-Install-Template.

## Installation

Module-Install-Template installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is
set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan Module::Install::Template

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

## Documentation

Module-Install-Template documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Module::Install::Template

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

